# 🗺️ System Architecture: Multi-Container Orchestration

Notes on designing, clustering, and managing multi-tiered application environments locally and in cloud staging.

## Why Orchestration Matters
* **Declarative Networking:** Defines the entire application stack configuration (services, volumes, open networks) inside a single code tracking document (`docker-compose.yml`).
* **Service Isolation:** Enables containers to securely handle business transactions within an internal network mask while selectively exposing individual frontward gateways.

## Core Directives
* `services`: Specifies the individual execution cells to instantiate.
* `ports`: Handles network traffic exposure (`host_port:container_port`).
* `depends_on`: Sets explicit boot schedules so core data layers instantiate before application logic attaches.
